<body>
  <h1>Privacy Policy</h1>
  <p class="date">Last updated: May 15, 2026</p>

  <p>
    This Privacy Policy explains how Bind handles information when you use the app.
    Bind is designed to merge PDF files locally on your device using Apple-provided
    system tools and frameworks.
  </p>

  <h2>Information We Collect</h2>
  <p>
    Bind does not collect, store, sell, share, or transmit any personal information.
    The app does not require account registration and does not collect your name,
    email address, location, contacts, identifiers, or usage data.
  </p>

  <h2>PDF Files and Local Processing</h2>
  <p>
    Any PDF files you select are processed locally on your device. The app uses the
    selected files only for the purpose of combining them into a new merged PDF file.
  </p>

  <p>
    Your PDF files are not uploaded to any server, cloud service, third-party service,
    or external database by Bind.
  </p>

  <h2>File Access</h2>
  <p>
    Bind only accesses the files that you manually select through the app. The app does
    not scan your device, access unrelated files, or modify your original PDF files unless
    you choose to save or export a new merged PDF.
  </p>

  <h2>Third-Party Services</h2>
  <p>
    Bind does not use third-party analytics, advertising networks, tracking tools, or
    external data processing services.
  </p>

  <h2>Tracking</h2>
  <p>
    Bind does not track you across apps or websites owned by other companies.
  </p>

  <h2>Data Sharing</h2>
  <p>
    Since Bind does not collect personal data, no personal data is shared with third parties.
  </p>

  <h2>Data Retention</h2>
  <p>
    Bind does not retain your personal data or your PDF files. Any output file is saved only
    in the location you choose on your device.
  </p>

  <h2>Children's Privacy</h2>
  <p>
    Bind does not knowingly collect any personal information from children.
  </p>

  <h2>Changes to This Privacy Policy</h2>
  <p>
    This Privacy Policy may be updated from time to time. Any changes will be posted on this
    page with an updated revision date.
  </p>

  <h2>Contact</h2>
  <p>
    If you have any questions about this Privacy Policy, you may contact the developer through
    the support contact provided on the App Store listing for Bind.
  </p>
</body>
</html>


